<paragraph id="E376062BFFD4FFE6FC68B05AFAD2054E" blockId="6.[968,1335,351,375]" box="[968,1335,351,375]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
<heading id="B83EB147FFD4FFE6FC68B05AFAD2054E" bold="true" box="[968,1335,351,375]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FC68B05AFAD2054E" authority="Bleeker, 1860" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[968,1335,351,375]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FC68B05AFAD2054E" bold="true" box="[968,1335,351,375]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FC68B05AFB72054E" bold="true" box="[968,1175,351,375]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Gobius melanopus</emphasis>
Bleeker, 1860
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E376062BFFD4FFE6FCE1B09AFB7806EF" blockId="6.[833,1472,415,726]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
Castelnau painting No. 193 (
<figureCitation id="7BF21AAEFFD4FFE6FBDAB09AFB2D058F" box="[1146,1224,415,438]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="5.[111,155,2033,2054]" captionTargetBox="[111,1449,297,1997]" captionTargetId="figure-64@5.[111,1449,297,1997]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs. 10–17. Figures 10, 11: dried mounted specimens in the collection of the Zoological Museum of the University of Liège, Beligium (ZMUL), catalogue numbers 2378a and 2378b. Figures 12–17: Castlenau’s paintings, numbers 163, 171, 482, 483, 625 and 193, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5342439" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5342439/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) is labeled as “ 
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FAD2B09AFC7605EF" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FAD2B09AFA5A058F" authority="Russell &amp; Fraser &amp; Larson, 2010" authorityName="Russell &amp; Fraser &amp; Larson" authorityYear="2010" box="[1394,1471,415,438]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="sp. nov.">Gobius</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CA8E6742FFD4FFE6FCE1B0BAFC7605EF" box="[833,915,447,470]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
” and “ 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FC7FB0BAFB0305EF" authority="Cast." authorityName="Cast." box="[991,1254,447,470]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FC7FB0BAFB4205EF" box="[991,1191,447,470]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Gobius melanopus</emphasis>
Cast.
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FB57B0BAFA2505EF" box="[1271,1472,447,470]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FB57B0BAFA2505EF" box="[1271,1472,447,470]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Gobius melanopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Bleeker in 1860c, based on Castelnau’s figure and the name attributed to Castelnau. No 
<typeStatus id="3C72B889FFD4FFE6FA95B0FAFA86062F" box="[1333,1379,511,534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">type</typeStatus>
material is known. The species name has been used as a valid name by Larson (in Randall &amp; Lim 2000: 637); where it was cited as ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FCC6B35AFC1A064F" box="[870,1023,607,630]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FCC6B35AFC1A064F" box="[870,1023,607,630]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Cryptocentrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FBAEB35AFB67064F" box="[1038,1154,607,630]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FBAEB35AFB67064F" box="[1038,1154,607,630]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">melanopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as at that time it was thought that the species name may refer to a group of species that include 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FC39B39AFB9A068F" baseAuthorityName="Cantor" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[921,1151,671,694]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="russus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FC39B39AFB9A068F" box="[921,1151,671,694]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Cryptocentrus russus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FB19B39AFAC5068F" baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[1209,1312,671,694]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="voigtii">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FB19B39AFAC5068F" box="[1209,1312,671,694]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">C. voigtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– species that may belong to a separate genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ABD355A0FFD4FFE6FCE1B3FAFB3B00EF" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" type="description">
<paragraph id="E376062BFFD4FFE6FCE1B3FAFB3B00EF" blockId="6.[833,1472,767,1238]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">
The species illustrated by Castelnau agrees with 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FA8BB3FAFB61070F" authority="Bleeker, 1876" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1876" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leptocephalus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FA8BB3FAFC3F070F" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Cryptocentrus leptocephalus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD4FFE6FC44B21AFB61070F" author="Bleeker, P" box="[996,1156,799,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="138 - 148" refId="ref6694" refString="Bleeker, P., 1876. Description de quelques especes insulindiennes inedites des genres Oxyurichthys, Paroxyurichthys et Cryptocentrus. Verslagen en Mededeelingen der Koninklijke Akademie van Wetenschappen. Afdeling Natuurkunde Amsterdam, Series. 2, 9: 138 - 148." type="journal article" year="1876">Bleeker, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="9BDE46BBFFD4FFE6FCE1B23AFC49076F" box="[833,940,831,854]" name="Singapore" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(RMNH 4665). Castelnau’s painting clearly shows the large pink spots and short pink streaks on the head, dorsal fins and pectoral fin base, dark anal fin, the oblique pinkish brown bars on the body, and the characteristic pinkish red and yellow-striped pelvic fins with blackish tips (compare with photos in Kuiter &amp; Tonozuka, 2001: 631; 
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD4FFE6FA9BB2DAFC03002F" author="Senou, H &amp; Suzuki, K" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" refId="ref8273" refString="Senou, H., T. Suzuki, K. Shibukawa, &amp; K. Yano, 2004. A photographic guide to the gobioid fishes of Japan. Heibonsha: Tokyo. 534 pp." type="book" year="2004">Senou et al., 2004: 316–317</bibRefCitation>
). Hence, 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FBEBB2FAFC60000F" authority="Bleeker, 1860 c" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FBEBB2FAFABA002F" box="[1099,1375,1023,1046]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">Cryptocentrus melanopus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD4FFE6FAC6B2FAFC60000F" author="Bleeker, P" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="446 - 456" refId="ref6399" refString="Bleeker, P., 1860 c. Derde bijdrage tot de kennis der vischfauna van Singapoera. Natuurkundig Tijdschrift voor Nederlandsche- Indie, 20: 446 - 456." type="journal article" year="1860">Bleeker, 1860c</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is the senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="24C97DA8FFD4FFE6FB08B51AFC9E006F" authority="Bleeker, 1876" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1876" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Cryptocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leptocephalus">
<emphasis id="D1BDDA39FFD4FFE6FB08B51AFAB8000F" box="[1192,1373,1055,1078]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="99">C. leptocephalus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="87587BDAFFD4FFE6FAC6B51AFC9E006F" author="Bleeker, P" pageId="6" pageNumber="99" pagination="138 - 148" refId="ref6694" refString="Bleeker, P., 1876. Description de quelques especes insulindiennes inedites des genres Oxyurichthys, Paroxyurichthys et Cryptocentrus. Verslagen en Mededeelingen der Koninklijke Akademie van Wetenschappen. Afdeling Natuurkunde Amsterdam, Series. 2, 9: 138 - 148." type="journal article" year="1876">Bleeker, 1876</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Under the 2000 ICZN Code, precedence must be maintained, as reversal of precedence (Article 23.9) cannot be met since the senior synonym has been used as a valid name after 1899 (although the junior synonym has been used for the species by at least 10 authors).
</paragraph>
